def CI_prop(s, n):
    p = s / n
    se2 = p * (1-p) / n
    se = np.sqrt(se2)
    low = p - 1.96 * se
    up = p + 1.96 * se
    print('Sample proportion is:', p)
    print('95% CI is: ({}, {})'.format(low, up))

def CI_mean_diff(without_limits_income, with_limits_income):
    s1 = np.var(without_limits_income)
    s2 = np.var(with_limits_income)
    n1 = len(without_limits_income)
    n2 = len(with_limits_income)
    se2 = s1/n1 + s2/n2
    se = np.sqrt(se2)

    diff = np.mean(without_limits_income) - np.mean(with_limits_income)
    low = diff - 1.96 * se
    up = diff + 1.96 * se
    print("The average difference is:", diff)
    print("The 95% CI is: ({}, {})".format(low, up))

CI_mean_diff(without_limits_income, with_limits_income)

def CI_prop(s, n):
    p = s / n
    se2 = p * (1-p) / n
    se = np.sqrt(se2)
    low = p - 1.96 * se
    up = p + 1.96 * se
    print('Sample proportion is:', p)
    print('95% CI is: ({}, {})'.format(low, up))
